<TITLE> Youth murdered for mobile phone </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka,Nov{bdnews24.com) - Two men have been arrested for the murder of a 17 year old youth identified as Saddam Hossain in the Mohammadpur area of the capital after attempting to steal his mobile phone, local police said. Police arrested Masud Rana and one Russel following the discovery of a body floating in an area of shallow water close to Lalmatia Bibi Masjid at 8.30 Saturday morning. Shusil Chandra Burman, from Mohammadpur Police Station, told bdnews24.com that the arrested men confessed to calling Saddam by mobile phone on Thursday evening. "He went out following the call and never returned, his father then lodged a general diary at the police station," said Burman. "Family members identified Saddam's body, which was marked by knife injuries on different parts of his body," added the police officer. Saddam's father, Yasin Mea, told bdnews24.com that they killed him after snatching his mobile phone. "His mobile phone was found with them. Saddam worked as a salesman at a local cloth shop," added Yasin. bdnew
